  "title": "1 year contract Associate Scientist, Cell Culture (Pharma) - Up to $4K #HKH",
  "description": "<p><strong>Associate Scientist, Cell Culture </strong></p><p>The candidate will work in a diverse team to support and troubleshoot commercial biologics cell culture manufacturing processes. The successful candidate will have experience in cell culture, excellent communication skills, and a collaborative mindset toeffectively work with cross-functional groups.</p><p><strong>Key responsibilities include:</strong></p><ul><li>Manufacturing process trending, participating in process validation activities, providing technical support, drafting technical justifications and process understanding by processmapping</li><li>Additional activities include the design, execution, and interpretation of experiments to perform process characterization, evaluate novel technologies, identify process improvements, drafting risk assessments and providing technical expertise to support regulatory submissions</li><li>A basic understanding of cell culture or fermentation biology, process scale-up and statistical methods is essential.</li><li>Hands-on experience working in the lab, aseptic technique, cell culture and bioreactor operations, to support the routine responsibilities with solid scientific data is also desirable.</li><li>The position necessitates extensive interaction with manufacturing, quality, purification process development as well as CMC/Regulatory Affairs groups</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements </strong></p><ul><li>Min Degree in Science </li><li>Min 1 to 3 years of working experience / internship in pharma plant </li></ul><p><strong>$3.5K + $500 site allowance</strong><br /><strong>Office hours, mon to Fri office hours </strong></p><p>Interested candidates, please forward your resume to <strong>kevynhuang@recruitexpress.com.sg </strong><br /></p><p>Consultant: Huang Jingsheng Kevyn (R1333338) <br />Recruit Express Pte Ltd (99C4599) </p>",
